    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Royal College of Physicians | London S.W.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>May 9<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. 1879</date>
                    <salute>Sir,</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                    <p>I have the honour to inform you that at a Meeting of the College held this day to award the “Baly Medal” “to the person who shall be deemed to have most distinguished himself in the science of Physiology” the Medal has been unanimously awarded to yourself.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
                    <p>It has been customary for the President of the College to present the Medal after the Harveian Oration which will be delivered on the 26<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> of June, and it is hoped that it will be convenient to you to be present on that occasion<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>I have the honour to be | Your obedient Servant | Henry A Pitman | Registrar <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/></p>
<p rend="left">Charles Darwin Esq</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="annotations">
                <note><hi rend="italic">Top of letter</hi>: ‘Keep’ <hi rend="italic">pencil</hi></note>
            </div>
            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The Baly medal, a biennial award, was founded from a gift received in 1866 from <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1439.xml">Frederick Daniel Dyster</ref> (<hi rend="italic">British Medical Journal</hi>, 4 November 1911, p. 1222). The award memorialised <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_8703.xml">William Baly</ref>, a physician who had died in a train accident in 1861 (<hi rend="italic">ODNB</hi>).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">The Harveian oration, established by <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_5856.xml">William Harvey</ref> in 1656, was an annual lecture held at the <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4101.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Royal College of Physicians</ref> of London (<hi rend="italic">ODNB</hi>). The president of the <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4101.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Royal College of Physicians</ref> in 1879 was <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_8337.xml">James Risdon Bennett</ref>.</note>    
        </div>  
      
